commentAnnotations.text: The Columbia Suicide Severity Rating Scale (C-SSRS) will be administered to all ongoing subjects at all remaining scheduled visits in Run In and Blinded treatments, and Rescue weeks 0, 8, 12, 16, and up to and including the EOT/ET and/or the EOS visit.
For Taiwan only: Similar to China, other countries in Asia, such as Taiwan, have a high prevalence of HBsAg negative, HBcAb positive, and HBsAb positive serology.
These changes are in effect for China only: Subjects who are HBsAg negative, HBcAb positive, and HBsAb positive at Screening will have reflex testing for HBV DNA.
